FortyTwo BBS on Ubuntu 25.10
============================

Supported development platform
------------------------------

Ubuntu 25.10 on x86_64 hardware is currently the only tested development
platform for FortyTwo BBS.

No other Linux distribution, Linux version, processor architecture or BSD
system is currently documented as supported or compatible.

Additional platforms will be tested after the first public release.


Development status
------------------

FortyTwo BBS is pre-alpha software intended exclusively for development,
code review and isolated testing.

There is currently no supported production installation or upgrade
procedure.

Do not run the inherited SETUP.sh script. It still implements the historical
MBSE BBS installation model, creates legacy system accounts and modifies
system configuration files.


Build requirements
------------------

A developer build on Ubuntu 25.10 requires at least:

- GCC and the standard C development toolchain
- GNU Make
- a POSIX-compatible shell
- glibc development headers
- Git and the required Autoconf build files

Optional features may use:

- zlib development files
- bzip2 development files
- iconv support
- GeoIP development files
- external archive programs
- external editors
- external virus scanners

The exact package list and automated installation procedure are still being
reviewed and will be documented only after they have been reproduced on a
clean Ubuntu 25.10 test system.


Network access
--------------

Telnet and SSH access have been tested locally on Ubuntu 25.10.

The current examples listen only on localhost and are available under:

examples/fortytwo-access

SSH is restricted to registered users and starts only FortyTwo BBS through a
forced command.

New-user registration remains disabled until operating-system account
creation has been isolated and hardened.


